# Implementation Standards (summary)

Full SoT: `docs/engineering/implementation-standards.md`

## Non-negotiables for API & backend code

1. **User-facing handlers never fan out** to N upstream HTTP calls — read Postgres materialized data or enqueue `ingest_job`.
2. **Cache before Claude** — `aurora_narration_log` / quota paths first.
3. **Parallel independent I/O** — `Promise.all` in RSC; no sequential waterfall.
4. **Idempotent cron + upsert** — safe retries; indexed lookups.
5. **Correct algorithm on hot paths** — if medium-term need (drift, backtest, macro DB, ingest queue), **implement the better design** even at higher short-term cost; log deferrals in journal only with Ray scope.

## Cohort hot paths

- Macro dashboard / series API
- Aurora narration + chat
- Shape C cron
- Future: OHLCV ingest worker, drift calc

## PR gate

Agent PRs touching `src/app/api/**`, `src/lib/macro/**`, `src/lib/aurora/**`, workers, or migrations must confirm implementation-standards checklist §8.

## Anti-patterns

IP-1 live API fan-out · IP-2 Claude without cache · IP-3 unbounded cron scan · IP-4 O(n²) portfolio on load · IP-5 defer v2 data platform without journal
